{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0a3e1867-15db-4d70-9128-7a2bed6a6403","content":"Found **1 untestable static** in your project:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\nThis is called directly, making it hard to mock in tests.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Use Django's `timezone.now()` (which is easier to mock via `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`) or inject the clock as a dependency:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis also fixes a subtle bug: `datetime.now()` returns a naive datetime, while `timezone.now()` returns a timezone-aware one — which Django expects when `USE_TZ = True`.\n\nWant me to apply this fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ae6fd64e-32b9-4a4c-9285-f695332b26f7","outputTokens":191,"requestId":"1BCD:AAEEE:AEE0B0:C5D896:6A03EEB3"},"id":"b6d5d70c-3a7f-4fa6-a1ba-88b0de29c3eb","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:23:36.245Z","parentId":"142171b5-dfcc-4576-b20f-661de017d6d4"}
